  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Slice the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, keeping the green stalks on, then score the<strong> </strong>flesh in a criss-cross pattern</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine halves</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1642518108969-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1642518108969-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1642518108969-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1642518108969-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1642518108969-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the aubergine is cooking, peel and chop the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> wedges</p><p>Cut the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> wedges</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> lamb mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1642518116301-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1642518116301-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1642518116301-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1642518116301-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1642518116301-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve <strong>half</strong> the <strong>beef stock mix </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and the<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>ground cumin</strong> to the lamb with the <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> dried oregano</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> with a grind of <strong>pepper</strong>, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 15 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>Turkish-style</strong> <strong>lamb stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
